stanford journal of law science and policy stanford law school stanford law school search utility navigation test directory news center library events publications contact & maps information for prospective students alumni employers current students faculty & staff pubs & blogs stanford journal of law science and policy go back overview the stanford journal of law science and policy is a peer reviewed journal for innovative interdisciplinary scholarship that bridges the divide between legal and scientific scholarship the semiannual journal provides a unique opportunity for scientists and legal scholars to write together and is freely available online to ensure a broad readership the journal is founded on the recognition that the challenges facing today's policy makers are complex for both scientific and political reasons and that the search for solutions will require pioneering cross disciplinary collaboration as one of the only sources for practical relevant thinking of this type the journal will be a valuable resource for policy makers one of the journal's key audiences for more information contact hannah shearer editor in chief tristan ursell managing editor danny cullenward elliot wolf submissions editor recorded & past events october 2009 stanford journal of law science & policy stem cell policy symposium october 3 2009 from 9 00 am 2 00 pm stanford journal of law science & policy stem cell policy symposium october 2 2009 from 8 30 pm 8 00 pm related information and recordings stanford journal of law science & policy stem cell policy symposium october 1 2009 from 10 00 am 11 00 pm april 2009 stanford journal of law science & policy general meeting april 20 2009 from 12 30 pm 1 30 pm climate change and marine systems managing for resiliency april 10 2009 from 8 15 am 5 00 pm contact information stanford law school stanford journal of law science & policy website cloudy 62 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
